description:
Define a thin Backend trait that the codegen core uses to pick a Module impl:

  pub trait Backend {
      type Module: cranelift_module::Module;
      fn module(&mut self) -> &mut Self::Module;
      fn finalize(self) -> Result<CompiledArtifact, CodegenError>;
  }

JIT impl: wraps JITModule, finalizes via `finalize_definitions` + `get_finalized_function`; produces an in-memory CompiledModule. compile() becomes `compile<B: Backend>(module: &Module, backend: B) -> Result<B::Output, CodegenError>`.

## Acceptance

- cargo test green.
- A second Backend impl is just an empty shell now (no AOT yet) — but the JIT path runs through the trait, proving the abstraction is real.
- compile_fn doesn't change after this; the wrapping was done in 4.5.
